Pre-heat your #oven{} to 180 degrees and bring a large #pot{} of water to the boil with 
@salt{1/4%tsp}. Peel and finely chop your @garlic clove{1}(peeled and finely chopped). 
Finely chop your @flat leaf parsley{3}(finely chopped) and @mint{3}(finely chopped) and 
grate the zest of half your @lemon{1/2}(zested). Chop your @potato{1} into 2cm chunks 
(no need to peel).

Mix together your chopped garlic, parsley, mint, lemon zest and @dukkah mix{3} in a 
#bowl{} along with @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of @pepper{good grind}.

Drizzle @oil{1%tbsp} onto a #baking tray{}, put your @pork medallion{2} onto the 
baking tray and press the herby dukkah mix onto the top of your pork. Put in the 
oven to cook for ~{15%minutes}.

Pop your potatoes into your boiling water and cook for ~{12-15%minutes} until cooked.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain, pop back in the pot and add in @?butter{1%tbsp}. 
Crush lightly with a #fork{} and season with a @salt{pinch} and a grind of 
@pepper{good grind}.

Drizzle @olive oil{1%tbsp}, @lemon juice{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and a good grind of 
@pepper{good grind} over your @mixed salad{1}.

Serve the crusted pork with your potatoes and your salad on the side. Enjoy!